items.title: In Assad's hometown, few shared in his family's fortune. They hope they won't share in his downfall
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
On the walls of the palatial mausoleum built to house the remains of former Syrian President Hafez Assad, vandals had sprayed variations of the phrase “Damn your soul, Hafez.” Near two weeks after the ouster of his son, ex-President Bashar Assad, people streamed in to take photos next to the burned-out hollow where the elder Assad’s grave used to be.

items.title: LIVE: Amazon workers strike in Queens, New York
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Live from Queens, New York, as Amazon workers affiliated with the Teamsters union launched a strike at seven of the company’s delivery hubs less than a week before Christmas.

The Teamsters said the workers, who voted to authorize strikes in recent days, joined picket lines after Amazon ignored a Sunday deadline the union had set for contract negotiations.

#amazon #news #live

items.title: Macron met with boos over Cyclone Chido response during visit to Mayotte
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
French President Emmanuel Macron met with locals on the Indian Ocean archipelago of Mayotte during his visit on Thursday to survey the devastation wreaked by Cyclone Chido. In Pamandzi, Macron spoke to residents whose homes were wrecked in the strongest cyclone to hit the region in nearly a century.

Some members of the crowd booed the president, angry at the French government's response to the disaster which they claim has been slow. Read more: https://bit.ly/4iF5mgR
